HEADWORD: Okinawa
<hw>Okinawa</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the largest island
of the central <membof>Ryukyu Islands</membof>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A campaign in the closing days of World War II in
the Pacific (April-June 1945); in savage close-quarter fighting US
marines and regular army troops took the island from the Japanese;
considered the greatest victory of the Pacific campaign for the
Americans.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Okinawa campaign.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Okra</ent>⟦br⟧
